responseText: NSLOCTEXT("[70199B914E7E03A9706A1499CF20B1FD]", "580981DF45DD6EB1056BB793EC475567", "Zinjala, reckless fool, called spirit to Horn, tried bind it. He failed. His mistake turned Horn dark, twisted what was pure. He was elder of strength, once part of our hope, now lost to shadows. His pride, his anger, trapped him in old ways. He could have led us forward, but he chose to fall. It is great sorrow. You have done much, Godling, but danger remains. Horn is cursed, and curse must be cleansed before it spreads further.")
name: DD_0110_EotGH_Wiyakoni_27_Response
